{"lemma":"شَجِيَّةٍ","slug":"شَجِيَّةٍ","root":"ش.ج.#","root_slug":"ش-ج-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ج-_","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21787","n21793"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21787","headword_ar":"شَجِىَ","root":"$jw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajFA","text_ar":"شَجًا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was choked;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his throat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fauces, became obstructed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. a bone or the like. (K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayoka biAlkaZomi walawo $ajiyta biAlEaZomi","text_ar":"عَلَيْكَ بِالكَظْمِ وَلَوْ شَجِيتَ بِالعَظْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keep thou to self-restraint though thou be choked by the bone"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And, [hence, by a metaphor, (see Har p. 33,)] aor. and inf. n. as above, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He grieved, mourned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lamented;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was sorrowful, sad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unhappy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, anxious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disquieted in mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-  Also, aor. and inf. n. as above, said of a creditor ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariym","text_ar":"غَرِيم"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went away,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K. [See 4.])       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajaA bayonahumo","text_ar":"شَجَا بَيْنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, an occasion of contention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of disagreement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difference, between them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajaAhu","text_ar":"شَجَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajowN","text_ar":"شَجْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) [app. originally"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ojaAhu","text_ar":"اَشْجَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the first of the senses assigned to the latter in the next paragraph: ―         -b2-  and hence,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(anxiety, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grieved him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused him to mourn"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lament,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be sorrowful"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sad"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unhappy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$jAhu","text_ar":"اشجاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) And, said of wealth ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlginaY","text_ar":"الغِنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"), inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajowN","text_ar":"شَجْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It excited his griefs, mournings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his desire."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$jAhu","text_ar":"اشجاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It caused him to be mirthful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excited him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, TA.) Thus each of these verbs has two contr. significations. (K.) But MF observes that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tar~abahu","text_ar":"طَرَّبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the explanation here given in the K, is said by the author of the K [in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Trb","text_ar":"طرب"},{"kind":"text","text":"] to denote a lightness arising from joy or grief. (TA.) [Generally, however, it means as rendered above.]"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Ks","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n21793","headword_ar":"شَجِىٌّ","root":"$jw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}